                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.2511/461: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-18T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 18, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. The Foreign Office expressed concern yesterday whether <persName
                        corresp="#p_EBE1">Edwards</persName> would be able promptly to regularize
                    his status as Chilean Chargé d’Affaires in Washington. I do not know what
                    difficulty is feared but it may be the absence of recognition. The Foreign
                    Office will appreciate anything you can do to facilitate this matter since they
                    do not desire to leave <persName corresp="#p_BVO1">Blanco Viel</persName> in
                    charge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
